author: stefan2
msg: On the fsx-1.10 branch:  Split svn_fs_x__get_dag_path into two functions,
one for actually returning the full dag_path_t and another for returning
the final DAG node only.  Individually, both functions are now much simpler
that the former combined one.
* subversion/libsvn_fs_x/dag_cache.h
(svn_fs_x__dag_path_flags_t): Remove flags for optimized code paths that
would be used only by single node lookup.
(svn_fs_x__get_dag_path): Update docstring.
* subversion/libsvn_fs_x/dag_cache.c
(svn_fs_x__get_dag_path): Remove all the single-DAG node code paths.
(walk_dag_path): New.  Copy of the former svn_fs_x__get_dag_path with
all path build-up logic removed.
(svn_fs_x__get_dag_node): Call the new function.
* subversion/libsvn_fs_x/tree.c
(x_closest_copy): Update flag from caller - that optimized code path no
longer exisits.
